---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Community & Coordination"
  description="Why I'm reaching out to kansascitymesh.net operators and what collaboration could look like."
>
  <!-- Primary Message -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2>This isn't a land grab.</h2>
    <p>
      I noticed kansascitymesh.net exists but appears inactive with no visible contact information. I don't know who you are or if you're still working on mesh networking in Kansas City. But if you're out there, I want to collaborate—not compete.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm one person building mesh infrastructure independently. I deployed my first router on the east side, and I'm documenting everything here so others can join. This site serves two purposes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Resource hub:</strong> Help anyone in KC who wants to deploy Meshtastic nodes</li>
      <li><strong>Coordination signal:</strong> Make it easy for existing operators (especially kansascitymesh.net) to find and contact me</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Possible Scenarios -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">What collaboration could look like</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Scenario 1: You're active, I didn't find you</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Maybe you have a Discord, Matrix chat, or local meetings I haven't discovered. <strong>Perfect.</strong> Point me to your community and I'll redirect traffic there. I'd rather join something established than build in parallel.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Scenario 2: You've been quiet, want to restart</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Life happens, projects pause. If you want to pick things back up, let's coordinate. I'll point this domain to kansascitymesh.net or work together under a shared umbrella. Your choice.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Scenario 3: You're done, happy to pass the torch</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          If you've moved on and want someone else to take the lead, I'm here. I'll keep building infrastructure and documenting everything. If you ever want to transfer the .net domain, I'd be honored—but no pressure.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Scenario 4: You registered it for "someday"</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Maybe you grabbed the domain with good intentions but haven't started yet. Great! Let's build together. I've got one router running and three more planned. You'd be joining something already in motion.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why This Matters -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-sunset-amber/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-sunset-amber/5 to-prairie-gold/5 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-sunset-amber/10 dark:to-prairie-gold/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Why I care about coordination</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      <p>
        <strong>Mesh networks work better when people coordinate.</strong> If there are multiple operators in KC working independently, we should know about each other. We can share coverage data, coordinate router placements, and avoid duplicating infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>I don't want to accidentally compete with existing work.</strong> If you've been building quietly and I didn't find you, that's my fault for not looking hard enough. I'd rather support what exists than create confusion by running in parallel.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>A single, clear resource benefits everyone.</strong> Right now, someone searching for "Kansas City Meshtastic" finds scattered forum posts and no clear entry point. One coordinated effort (whether that's mine, yours, or ours together) serves the community better.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact Methods -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">How to reach me</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      I'm monitoring multiple channels. Use whichever you prefer:
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Email (Public)</div>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-sm text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">contact@kansascitymesh.live</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">General inquiries, partnership discussions</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Signal/Matrix</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Details on contact page</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">Encrypted messaging for sensitive coordination</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">On-Mesh Contact</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Node: KC-MESH-R1</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-ink-600 dark:text-cream-200">Direct message if you're already on the mesh</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-mesh-green/10 border border-mesh-green/30 p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>Response commitment:</strong> I check these daily. If you reach out, you'll hear back within 24 hours—usually much faster.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Timeline & Transparency -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Status & Timeline</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-mesh-green bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-500 dark:text-cream-200">January 2025</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Site launched, Router 1 operational</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">First infrastructure deployed on KC east side. Reached out to visible Meshtastic operators via forums and Discord.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-kc-blue bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-kc-sky dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-500 dark:text-cream-200">Current Status</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Active outreach, building documentation</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">Monitoring for kansascitymesh.net operator contact. Documenting deployment process. Planning Router 2 on west side.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-ink-300 bg-surface-100 p-5 dark:border-ink-600 dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-500 dark:text-cream-200">If No Contact by March 2025</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Proceed with independent buildout</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">If no coordination contact by then, I'll assume solo operation and continue deploying the 4-router backbone. Invitation remains open indefinitely.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I'm NOT Doing -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-kc-red/30 bg-surface-100 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-sunset-amber/30 dark:bg-sand-900">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">What I'm NOT doing</h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span> Claiming to be "the" Kansas City mesh network</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span> Trying to take over or discredit existing work</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span> Building a "competing" organization</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span> Gatekeeping who can deploy nodes in KC</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">✗</span> Requiring "membership" or formal registration</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      <strong>This is just infrastructure and documentation.</strong> Anyone can deploy Meshtastic nodes anywhere, anytime. I'm building routers, documenting the process, and making it easy for others to join. That's it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Ready to connect?</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        If you're the kansascitymesh.net operator—or anyone else working on mesh in KC—I want to hear from you.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/community/contact"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-8 py-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
      >
        Contact Me
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
